Hello Hiba,  Thank you for your kind words about my post and for reaching out to me. I am glad to hear that my project is of interest to your research.  Regarding your questions about handling null data, the best practice is to first check for the proportion of missing data and the pattern of missing data, this could be done by using libraries like missingno in python. After that, if the missing data is MCAR (Missing completely at random) this could be handled by removing the samples with missing values or by using imputation techniques like mean or median imputation or more sophisticated methods such as multiple imputation. However, if the missing data is not MCAR (Missing not at random) then it's better to use imputation methods such as Predictive mean matching or k-nearest neighbor imputation. Additionally, it's always important to check the imputed data for outliers and the distribution of the data.  Unforutantely I didn't include that part in my post because it's work in progress and my supervisor didn't allow it at least now.   Please let me know if you have any further questions or if there is anything else I can assist you with. CONVERSATION TITLE: العنوان الجهات التنظيمية ورواد الصناعة الإقليميين
CONTENT:
Ahmed عزيزي


ندعوك للمشاركة في مؤتمر (DIA Middle East) في نسخته الأولى في فبراير القادم واغتنام الفرصة بالاجتماع مع ممثلي الهيئات الصحية وخبراء الصناعة وأهل العلم وممثلي المرضى على منصة محايدة.


يهدف برنامج المؤتمر الذي تم تطويره بالتعاون الوثيق مع الهيئة العامة للغذاء والدواء بالمملكة العربية السعودية، تحفيز المناقشات وتعزيز التعاون وتقديم الحلول عبر دورة حياة تطوير الدواء من خلال ثمانية مسارات لمجالات مخصصة، بدءاً من الاستراتيجية التنظيمية والتقارب إلى اليقظة الدوائية والرقمنة والابتكار وتقييم تكنولوجيا الرعاية الصحية والجودة وسيقدم منصة رائعة من أجل المناقشات البناءة والتعاون بين جميع الجهات المعنية المتواجدة.


انضم إلينا من أجل:

✔️ التواصل مع مجموعة من ألمع العقول في المنطقة ومقابلة زملائك وتوسيع شبكة معارفك.

✔️ الاستماع إلى عدد لا حصر له من الجهات المعنية الأساسية في الصناعة وأهل العلم وممثلي المرضى وممثلي الهيئة الصحية وغير ذلك الكثير.

✔️ تحسين معرفتك بالموضوعات شديدة الأهمية مع مسارات المحتوى الثمانية والتي تشمل التقارب التنظيمي والإستراتيجية التنظيمية، وتكنولوجيا الرعاية الصحية، والكيمياء والتصنيع والضوابط، واليقظة الدوائية، والتجارب الإكلينيكية، والخدمات الرقمية والأجهزة، والقيمة وإمكانية الوصول وغير ذلك الكثير.

Dear Ahmed,

I am messaging on behalf of Dr. Alex Gardner-McTaggart, Course Director for The University of Manchester's MA Educational Leadership in Practice. I thought the MA may be of interest to you, given the skills and experience you list in your profile.

The MA has been developed as such that it is extremely well-placed to support professionals like yourself with your career goals and aspirations. You can study from anywhere in the world, where you would continue to work full-time in your current role. The MA in Educational Leadership in Practice is a part-time, blended programme, delivered mostly online, with conferences held twice a year at our Manchester Centre.

I would be delighted to arrange a personal consultation with Alex, if you would like further information on the programme.

If you are interested, please contact us by emailing studyonline@manchester.ac.uk or calling us on +44 (0)161 306 8333.

Reasons to choose the MA in Educational Leadership in Practice

  • Practical: Our online course is specifically designed for working professionals. It will equip you with the skills and tools needed to critically engage and support your educational initiatives, in addition to using a Practice-Based Learning approach to put into practice what it means to be an effective leader in education.
  • International: As a student at The University of Manchester, you’ll develop your global network. You’ll study online, share best practice, and learn alongside peers from around the world. You’ll also have the opportunity to connect and meet with fellow students during the workshops at our Manchester or Dubai centres, twice a year.
  • Flexible: Our part-time flexible learning format fits around your career and your lifestyle. It allows you to continue with your existing commitments, whilst earning a full Master’s qualification.
  • Faculty: All of our teaching staff have extensive practical experience and you will have the opportunity to learn from and work with some of our world-leading international education experts. You’ll also be provided with support throughout your studies with us. 

I look forward to heading from you.

With best wishes,

Amina Mufti on behalf of


Dr. Alex Gardner-McTaggart,

Course Director, MA Educational Leadership in Practice
